<br>
I wrote up a little analysis of the current state of affairs and posted it on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bjornstar.com/">my website</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. It looks like they were pretty careless about how everything lined up overall. Some of the level IV effects don't even exist.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I hope you'll find it a useful listing of focus effect names. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyidth>yyidth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/24/02 10:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP and the new state of Focus Effects</span><hr size=1> Quite well done. Thanks for the effort.<br>
<br>
They think we are bards though, changing out clothing based on what spell we are casting.<br>
<br>
-- <br>
Yyidth of the Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjornstar>bjornstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/24/02 1:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> If you've something to add...</span><hr size=1> If any of you wizards has any experience with any of these new focus effects please post your item stats and what spells the effect will activate on.<br>
<br>
It seems a lot of these effects have confusing descriptions and I'm trying to nail down precisely which spells each one affects.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bjornstar.com/">Diku Goldenmind</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Gnomish Enchanter Extraordinaire<br>
Fennin Ro - &lt;Regeneration X&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xanlith>xanlith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/02 7:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you've something to add...</span><hr size=1> Sanguine Preservation is a pretty lame effect. It only effects self buffs. We put it on our Enchanter expecting it to save him C3 mana but even if he cast it on his group by targetting himself the effect wouldnt trigger. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yyidth>yyidth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/02 11:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP and the new state of Focus Effects</span><hr size=1> I used your list to update my focus effect spreadsheet, and while digging around inside lucy noticed a few things.<br>
<br>
One is that the only focus level IV effects missing are the two Reanimation specific ones and the Reagent one. All others are in the database and act as expected on level 65 spells.<br>
<br>
Two is that the third cleric spell haste focus spell does work with level 65 spells.<br>
<br>
Three is that there is not really that much duplication of focus effects. Most focus effects that share appear the be the same when looking at the percentage of something they do are different in subtle ways. Like duration, casting time or class of spells they work with.<br>
<br>
For example, Shade Stone Focus is not a duplication of Blaze of the Lightbringer. Both have a 20% casting time haste, but Shade Stone Focus only effects instant cast spells. Whereas the other 4 dmg spell casting haste focus effects do not have this limitation. I assume this means that they will work with dots (which is something I find scary).<br>
<br>
Thanks again for the focus item web page, now I have just to add mage summoned focus effects and the new bard/wizard/cleric focus effects to my spreadsheet and it will be up to date.<br>
<br>
By the way, I read elsewhere that the new cleric line of spells does indeed stack with the item focus effects. Which seem to imply that the new wizard spell (30%, cold only) with have the same behavior. And, maybe the bard song (15%) will stack as well. Giving ice spear a 80% dmg increase. <p>-- <br>
Yyidth of the Rathe<br>
<br>
“He who fights against monsters should see to it that he does not become a monster in the process. And when you stare persistently into an abyss, the abyss also stares into you.”  —Friedrich Nietzsche</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjornstar>bjornstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/25/02 3:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoP and the new state of Focus Effects</span><hr size=1> Ahh you are right about Summoning Haste IV being in there, thanks.<br>
<br>
Lucy shows both <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3546&amp;source=Live">Affliction Efficiency IV</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3534&amp;source=Live">Affliction Haste IV</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> only affecting up to level 60.<br>
<br>
Thanks for catching that Cleric Haste error, it was late :P<br>
<br>
As far as focus effects stacking, there doesn't appear anything in the spell database that would show the cleric spells would stack with the focus items. It was stated before that no focus effects will stack, you will only use one effect of a certain type.<br>
<br>
What's the name of the bard songs that change casting??<br>
<br>
*edited grammatical errors*<br>
<br>
